verses.roman:
kibā kelāhala kare, bujhite nā pāri
kāhāke vā stuti kare--anumāna kari

synonyms: kibā—what; kelāhala—rowdy sounds; kare—they make; bujhite—to understand; nā—not; pāri—I am able; kāhāke—to whom; vā—or; stuti—prayer; kare—they offer; anumāna—guess; kari—I do.
translation: "They made noisy sounds I could not understand. I guess they were offering prayers to someone."
